Will, you and i are going
back to the candelas'.

13:08.000 --> 13:10.000
We're gonna profile
all of their associates.

13:11.000 --> 13:12.400
What should i do?

13:18.300 --> 13:19.900
I need you to
go home.

13:23.100 --> 13:24.400
Okay.

13:24.500 --> 13:27.100
But if you need me,
call...

13:28.300 --> 13:30.100
Even if
it's just to talk.

13:41.800 --> 13:43.400
Todd, honey...

13:43.500 --> 13:48.300
I really, really need you to focus on
calibrating your creative energy.

13:48.400 --> 13:51.100
Now by creative energy,
what do i mean?

13:51.100 --> 13:53.000
I mean the source
of your power.

13:53.000 --> 13:57.000
The source of your power,
todd, is you.

13:57.900 --> 13:59.000
How do you, mother.

13:59.000 --> 14:02.000
Hello. You're...
you're here.

14:02.900 --> 14:07.400
I'm just finishing up
a session in my office.

14:07.400 --> 14:10.000
I'm so flattered you have
my framed book covers

14:10.000 --> 14:11.200
In your office.

14:11.200 --> 14:15.700
Well, a coach
can never be too proud.

14:16.500 --> 14:18.900
Mr. Castle,
i just wanted to thank you

14:18.900 --> 14:24.200
For being so honest about your struggle
with persistent and chronic writer's block.

14:24.300 --> 14:24.800
Excuse me?

14:24.800 --> 14:28.300
Well, todd is
an aspiring novelist,

14:28.300 --> 14:33.200
So i shared with him your inspiring
tale of triumph over adversity.

14:33.500 --> 14:36.300
Well,
how courageous of me.

14:36.500 --> 14:37.500
Good luck, todd.

14:37.500 --> 14:38.600
Thanks.

14:39.000 --> 14:40.800
I'll take
the year-Long package.

14:41.000 --> 14:43.300
Way to be decisive, kiddo.
Good for you.

14:43.300 --> 14:44.500
- I'll see you next week.
- Thank you.

14:44.500 --> 14:46.800
- Nice to meet you.
- And remember, you is who you is.

14:46.800 --> 14:49.400
And if you ain't who you is,
who is you?

14:51.000 --> 14:55.700
Well, nice to see all those years
as an actress have really paid off.

14:55.800 --> 14:58.400
"Focus on calibrating
your creative energies"?

14:58.500 --> 15:00.000
I'll have you know,

15:00.000 --> 15:03.800
Todd is a very bright spirit
in need of direction.

15:03.800 --> 15:05.500
Mother, it's bad enough
that you're slandering me.

15:05.500 --> 15:09.300
Do you have to commandeer my office
to do your new age coddle session?

15:09.300 --> 15:12.600
Richard, you can't expect me
to pay manhattan rates for office space.

15:12.600 --> 15:14.300
Well, how about this?

15:14.300 --> 15:15.800
You cannot beat this location.

15:15.800 --> 15:19.000
Proximity to beverages
and sharp utensils.

15:19.000 --> 15:21.500
Sweetheart,
as your life coach,

15:21.500 --> 15:25.300
I have to urge you to say nay
to your inner naysayer.

15:26.100 --> 15:27.900
I call that a martha-Ism.

15:28.100 --> 15:30.000
How is it that you don't know
who my father is,

15:30.000 --> 15:31.900
You don't know how your
ex-Husband stole all your money,

15:31.900 --> 15:34.300
Yet you are giving life
coaching advice?

15:34.300 --> 15:37.300
Mistakes are the building
blocks of wisdom.

15:37.500 --> 15:40.500
A martha-Ism.
Besides, freud was an addict.

15:40.500 --> 15:42.500
Didn't stop him
from helping people.

15:42.500 --> 15:47.100
Sadly, faced with his mother's...
twisted yet unimpeachable logic,

15:47.300 --> 15:48.800
Richard castle's
head exploded.

15:48.900 --> 15:50.200
Ah, well.

15:51.800 --> 15:53.500
So why are you home
so early?

15:53.500 --> 15:55.300
Well, thought i'd take
a little breather.

15:55.300 --> 15:57.400
Working on a, uh,
kidnapping case.

15:57.400 --> 15:58.700
A little girl.

15:59.500 --> 16:01.300
No wonder you're so surly.

16:01.500 --> 16:04.200
Those poor parents,
having a child ripped away...

16:04.200 --> 16:05.900
I can't imagine
how they must feel.

16:06.000 --> 16:07.300
Is alexis home?

16:07.400 --> 16:08.800
She's upstairs.

16:08.900 --> 16:10.900
I'm feeling a deep-Seated
need for a hug.

16:10.900 --> 16:12.600
Perfectly understandable.

16:13.000 --> 16:14.900
After all,
we are pod-Mates.

16:15.000 --> 16:18.000
Another martha-Ism.
I call it the peapod bond--

16:18.000 --> 16:20.800
You know, the bond that exists
between parent and child--

16:20.800 --> 16:22.700
You and me,
you and alexis.

16:22.800 --> 16:25.400
We're all peas in a pod,
and whether we like it or not,

16:25.400 --> 16:28.500
Everyone who's ever had a child
is in the pod forever.

16:28.500 --> 16:30.000
The peapod bond.

16:31.000 --> 16:33.500
Alexis!
Thank you, mother.

16:33.800 --> 16:35.300
I'll deduct my session fee
from your rent.

16:35.300 --> 16:36.000
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

16:36.000 --> 16:38.000
You might want to consider
the year-Long package.

16:38.000 --> 16:39.200
It's a bargain!

16:44.100 --> 16:45.000
What was that for?

16:45.000 --> 16:46.800
Just a peapod thing.

16:47.000 --> 16:48.300
Gram will explain.

16:55.600 --> 16:56.600
Hey.

16:57.000 --> 16:59.300
Hey, yourself.
Want some?

16:59.800 --> 17:01.200
Yeah, thanks.

17:01.800 --> 17:03.500
So i just got word
from my guys,

17:03.500 --> 17:05.300
And ellers is a dead end.

17:06.700 --> 17:09.500
The owner over at
paradise diner on east 62nd vouched

17:09.500 --> 17:12.200
That he was having his usual
poached eggs this morning.

17:13.300 --> 17:14.800
Would have been
too easy, right?

17:16.700 --> 17:18.400
Or over easy?

17:23.000 --> 17:25.200
That's like something
castle would say.

17:26.500 --> 17:27.700
You like him.

17:32.300 --> 17:34.200
No, i just, um...

17:35.300 --> 17:36.700
I don't know.

17:37.100 --> 17:38.600
I think he's interesting.

17:38.800 --> 17:40.500
So you're not...

17:41.100 --> 17:43.900
Together? No.

17:48.400 --> 17:50.100
I meant to call.

17:50.800 --> 17:53.300
Must have picked up
the phone a dozen times.

17:55.700 --> 17:57.500
Yeah, i know. You meant
to do a lot of things.

17:57.500 --> 18:01.300
That's why you left,
remember?

18:02.200 --> 18:04.500
Boston was
a great opportunity.

18:04.500 --> 18:05.800
I'm not saying
that it wasn't.

18:05.800 --> 18:09.300
I'm just saying,
it was a choice...

18:09.600 --> 18:11.600
That didn't include me.

18:12.500 --> 18:13.700
You could have come.

18:13.800 --> 18:15.000
And then done what?

18:15.300 --> 18:18.200
Join the boston p.D., and then
you have to move to phoenix

18:18.200 --> 18:19.800
And then cleveland,
and then you're back here?

18:19.800 --> 18:23.200
I mean, we both know what
that life is all about.

18:24.800 --> 18:27.000
Didn't stop me
from missing you,

18:27.600 --> 18:29.300
Missing us.

18:29.700 --> 18:32.000
Sundays in the park...

18:32.100 --> 18:37.000
Those ridiculous neon ice skates
at rockefeller center.

18:38.100 --> 18:42.200
I will have you know that
those ice skates are awesome.

18:44.500 --> 18:46.300
It wasn't the skates.

18:51.200 --> 18:52.800
Will, i--

18:58.400 --> 19:01.100
Oh! I thought cops
and feds hated each other.

19:01.100 --> 19:03.900
They say justice never sleeps.
I think i know why.

19:03.900 --> 19:06.300
- We were just, uh--
- Being consenting adults.

19:06.300 --> 19:07.300
I'm not judging.

19:07.300 --> 19:08.700
I thought i told you
to go home.

19:08.700 --> 19:09.700
I did go home,

19:09.800 --> 19:11.700
But then my mother told me
something that couldn't wait.

19:11.700 --> 19:12.700
You live with your mother?

19:12.700 --> 19:14.100
Yeah, apparently,
we're peas in a pod.

19:14.200 --> 19:16.500
But the important point is,
angela is adopted.

19:16.500 --> 19:17.200
So?

19:17.200 --> 19:19.100
So prior to giving up her baby,

19:19.100 --> 19:21.800
The birth mother would have been
given background on the candelas,

19:21.800 --> 19:24.700
Specifically their ability to
support the child.

19:24.800 --> 19:26.600
Knowledge of their finances.

19:26.800 --> 19:28.200
Really, kate,

19:28.300 --> 19:31.300
We're gonna waste time
on the insights of nancy drew here?

19:31.300 --> 19:33.000
Is that supposed to
be an insult?

19:33.000 --> 19:34.700
Because nancy drew
solved every case.

19:35.200 --> 19:37.500
Look, okay,
and i'm quoting here,

19:37.700 --> 19:40.600
"When a child's life is
at stake, we have to be sure,

19:40.700 --> 19:43.200
Which means we have to question
everything we think we know."

19:43.300 --> 19:45.000
I was a junior
in high school.

19:45.000 --> 19:46.900
What was i gonna do
with a baby?

19:47.300 --> 19:49.500
It's been two years,
miss gomez.

19:51.000 --> 19:53.500
Two years
is still a long time

19:53.500 --> 19:55.800
To think about a decision
you made when you were 16.

19:55.800 --> 19:57.800
What am i doing here?
What is this about?

19:57.800 --> 20:01.200
We're talking about the baby
and your regretting your decision.

20:01.300 --> 20:02.700
My decision?

20:03.500 --> 20:05.300
I don't regret my decision.

20:05.500 --> 20:07.400
Then why did you
try to find her?

20:08.500 --> 20:10.300
What are you
talking about?

20:11.100 --> 20:15.000
This is a petion that you filed with
the adoption agency a couple of months ago.

20:16.100 --> 20:20.500
It's a form requesting the identity
of the adoptive parents of angela.

20:21.200 --> 20:24.000
- A signed form.
- No.

20:24.200 --> 20:25.800
- That's not my signature.
- Lucia, i'm not--

20:25.800 --> 20:28.700
No, really. Look,
you can see for yourself.

20:29.500 --> 20:31.400
That's not my signature.

20:32.300 --> 20:34.800
Why?
What's going on?

20:35.000 --> 20:36.400
What happened to her?

20:37.000 --> 20:37.800
Is she okay?

20:37.800 --> 20:40.700
Did anyone in your family object
to you giving up your baby?

20:40.700 --> 20:43.800
No, no one. My-- My mom
even helped me with it.

20:43.800 --> 20:45.100
And the father?

20:46.200 --> 20:47.400
Juan?

20:49.200 --> 20:51.200
He was in iraq
when i had her,

20:51.300 --> 20:53.200
But we talked about it.

20:54.200 --> 20:55.300
He was cool.

20:55.500 --> 20:57.100
Are you sure about that?

20:58.600 --> 21:00.200
He still in iraq?

21:00.300 --> 21:02.900
No, he got back
a couple months ago.

21:08.600 --> 21:10.100
Juan restrepo?

21:11.800 --> 21:14.200
Nypd. We'd like to
ask you some-- Oh!

21:14.300 --> 21:16.300
Go, go, go, go!
Hey!

21:17.100 --> 21:19.700
Freeze!
Hands up!

21:23.800 --> 21:24.600
Freeze!

21:24.700 --> 21:26.100
Keep your hands up!

21:28.000 --> 21:29.500
On the ground.
On the ground!

21:29.700 --> 21:31.200
Hit the ground!

21:34.300 --> 21:35.500
So why'd you run?

21:35.500 --> 21:36.500
Look,in my neighborhood,

21:36.500 --> 21:38.400
When you see a cop,
that's what you do.

21:41.300 --> 21:44.300
What? No, uh,
good cop/bad fed?

21:45.800 --> 21:47.300
The guy did two tours
in the gulf.

21:47.300 --> 21:50.100
I go over there, he'd turn it
into a pissing match.

21:50.100 --> 21:54.100
But kate, she's got a way
of sneaking up on people.

21:54.300 --> 21:55.800
You mean like
last night?

21:58.300 --> 21:59.200
Can you believe this?

21:59.300 --> 22:01.000
Dude details cars
for a living.

22:01.100 --> 22:03.300
You'd think he'd have
a little more pride in his ride.

22:05.800 --> 22:07.200
I'm just saying,

22:07.800 --> 22:10.100
It looked like
quite a kiss.

22:10.200 --> 22:12.400
- You jealous, castle?
- Me?

22:12.500 --> 22:15.700
No, but you have to admit...
i was right.

22:16.000 --> 22:19.600
You are jealous...
that i hooked her.

22:19.700 --> 22:22.800
What's there to be jealous of?
You couldn't reel her in.

22:23.300 --> 22:25.100
We'll see about that.

22:26.200 --> 22:28.800
I was 18 when lucia
got pregnant.

22:30.000 --> 22:33.000
Six months in,
i got deployed.

22:33.100 --> 22:35.400
I never even had
the chance to see her.

22:35.800 --> 22:38.100
But you signed
the adoption papers.

22:38.200 --> 22:41.100
You know, when you're over there,
you see so many kids.

22:41.200 --> 22:42.800
I just...

22:43.200 --> 22:44.600
I need to know
she was okay.

22:44.600 --> 22:49.000
I- I filled out the form,
and i put lucia's name instead.

22:49.200 --> 22:52.800
- You got an address.
- Yeah, dude felt bad for me.

22:53.100 --> 22:54.500
He was over there, too,
in gulf one,

22:54.500 --> 22:55.500
And he only lost an arm.

22:55.500 --> 22:57.000
And what did you lose?

22:58.800 --> 23:00.800
An i.E.D.
Hit my humvee.

23:01.500 --> 23:03.500
The shrapnel
tore through the floor.

23:03.700 --> 23:05.800
The doc says i'm never
gonna have kids of my own,

23:05.800 --> 23:07.100
So...

23:07.500 --> 23:10.000
Yeah, i got an address,
and i went to go see my daughter.

23:10.100 --> 23:13.900
So you kidnap her and you ask
her adoptive parents for money?

23:14.000 --> 23:15.500
Wait, "kidnap her"?
She was kidnapped?

23:15.500 --> 23:17.100
And you think
i did that?

23:17.200 --> 23:19.400
All i ever wanted to know
was that she was okay!

23:19.600 --> 23:21.100
Is she?!

23:24.100 --> 23:26.600
Yo. Birth dad?
His story checks out.

23:26.700 --> 23:29.000
Limo company had him doing
their fleet yesterday.

23:29.100 --> 23:31.700
I don't care.
He had motive and opportunity.

23:31.800 --> 23:33.700
His motive was
the instinct of fatherhood.

23:33.700 --> 23:35.000
If he took her,
he'd have been with her,

23:35.000 --> 23:36.800
Not at some $12-An-Hour
detailing job.

23:36.800 --> 23:38.800
Doesn't matter.
I want e.S.U. On his place.

23:38.800 --> 23:40.000
It's not him, will.

23:40.000 --> 23:43.000
We're at square freakin' one,
and we've got nothing.

23:43.000 --> 23:45.200
You can send e.S.U.
Wherever you want,

23:45.200 --> 23:47.000
But i'm not
losing this one.

23:49.300 --> 23:51.700
What did she mean,
"not losing this one"?

23:53.300 --> 23:55.000
The case we worked.

23:56.100 --> 23:58.000
I thought you got the guy.

23:59.300 --> 24:00.900
We did,
but...

24:01.300 --> 24:03.200
The kid was already dead.

24:08.700 --> 24:09.900
Sorenson.

24:10.500 --> 24:11.400
On my way.

24:12.600 --> 24:14.200
Another call
about the ransom.

24:15.500 --> 24:17.600
They asked for
75 packs of hundreds,

24:17.600 --> 24:20.700
Randomized serial numbers
and warned against bait money,

24:20.700 --> 24:22.300
Dye packs and trackers.

24:22.300 --> 24:23.600
Sounds like
they know your playbook.

24:23.600 --> 24:25.300
They were detailed
down to the make,

24:25.300 --> 24:27.600
Model and color
of the backpack.

24:27.600 --> 24:28.700
Drop instructions?

24:28.700 --> 24:30.000
We wait for their call.

24:30.000 --> 24:31.500
All right,
let's get the money set,

24:31.500 --> 24:33.000
Be ready to
make the drop.

24:33.100 --> 24:35.500
Why didn't they tell us
where to bring the money?

24:35.500 --> 24:37.600
They're testing you.
It's not unusual.

24:37.700 --> 24:39.300
Which means
before we make the drop,

24:39.300 --> 24:40.900
We'll need to test them.

24:41.000 --> 24:44.300
We'll need proof that
they have angela and that she's okay.

24:44.800 --> 24:46.400
What if
they don't give any?

24:46.600 --> 24:48.500
- What if they refuse?
- How can you think that?

24:48.500 --> 24:50.700
- I'm just saying--
- What, you think she's dead?

24:50.700 --> 24:52.800
- No, of course not.
- I should've gotten up.

24:52.800 --> 24:54.300
I shouldn't have
let you watch her.

24:54.300 --> 24:56.200
Don't tell me what to say!

24:56.200 --> 24:58.600
Tell me, alfred,
was it worth it?!

24:58.700 --> 25:01.200
Was it worth
our little girl?!

25:02.600 --> 25:04.200
Oh! Oh, my...

25:12.900 --> 25:14.400
Mrs. Candela?

25:16.600 --> 25:17.600
Theresa...

25:17.800 --> 25:20.000
You can't give in
to your fear.

25:20.300 --> 25:24.300
Neither you nor your husband
is responsible for what happened.

25:27.800 --> 25:28.700
Come on.

25:32.500 --> 25:35.700
Remember, no proof, no money.
We need to be firm on that.

25:36.100 --> 25:38.300
Okay?
Here we go.

25:40.100 --> 25:41.200
Hello.

25:41.300 --> 25:42.500
Listen carefully.

25:42.600 --> 25:45.400
Any deviation,
and your daughter dies.

25:45.600 --> 25:47.100
I understand.

25:47.300 --> 25:50.000
A civilian, not a cop,
must make the drop,

25:50.000 --> 25:51.500
Or we kill the girl.

25:51.600 --> 25:54.600
We see police or fbi,
and she dies.

25:54.600 --> 25:58.300
- Do you have the money?
- Yes. 750, like you said.

25:58.600 --> 25:59.800
Put it in the backpack

25:59.800 --> 26:03.500
And bring it to the northeast corner
of 1st avenue and 47th.

26:03.500 --> 26:06.600
There's a mailbox there with
a cell phone taped underneath.

26:06.600 --> 26:09.300
We'll text further instructions
once you're there.

26:09.500 --> 26:10.600
When we have the money,

26:10.600 --> 26:13.000
Then we'll call
with the girl's location.

26:13.300 --> 26:15.500
Ask for proof
that angela's okay.

26:16.100 --> 26:19.800
You won't get any money until
i know my little girl is okay.

26:21.000 --> 26:22.200
Mama?

26:23.800 --> 26:25.700
Hi, sweetheart.

26:25.800 --> 26:27.500
You have one hour.

26:33.500 --> 26:36.300
Once they get paid,
there's no incentive to keep her alive,

26:36.300 --> 26:37.800
So i'll make the drop.

26:38.000 --> 26:41.600
Figure, we'll place our people
at a 1-Block radius from the mailbox.

26:41.600 --> 26:42.700
No.

26:42.800 --> 26:44.100
They said no cops.

26:44.300 --> 26:46.500
It's okay.
I've done this before.

26:46.500 --> 26:48.000
And they won't know
i'm an fbi agent.

26:48.000 --> 26:49.500
And if they do?

26:49.600 --> 26:52.500
Mr. Candela, we need this
to go as smoothly as possible.

26:52.500 --> 26:54.100
She's my daughter,

26:54.100 --> 26:56.600
And we're gonna follow their
instructions to the letter.

26:56.600 --> 26:58.700
They said no cops.

27:01.100 --> 27:04.700
Look, i'm her father,

27:05.000 --> 27:07.000
And i can do this.

27:09.800 --> 27:11.900
Do i make myself clear?

27:19.500 --> 27:21.400
No way we can send
the father.

27:21.500 --> 27:23.600
Too many things could go wrong.
He's too emotional.

27:23.600 --> 27:25.100
What choice do we have?

27:25.100 --> 27:27.200
- Me.
- What?

27:28.000 --> 27:29.100
I'm not a cop.

27:29.200 --> 27:31.300
I'm certainly not emotional.

27:31.300 --> 27:32.800
No.
Absolutely not.

27:32.800 --> 27:35.000
The nypd already has
a signed waiver from me,

27:35.000 --> 27:38.400
And i don't like saying this,

27:38.500 --> 27:39.600
But you're running out of time.

27:39.600 --> 27:41.000
Castle's right.

27:41.100 --> 27:42.000
You can't be serious.

27:42.000 --> 27:44.000
He's been with me
on cases before.

27:44.000 --> 27:45.500
He's good under pressure.

27:46.300 --> 27:49.000
And he's our best shot.

28:17.000 --> 28:18.500
Okay, so this
is usually the part

28:18.500 --> 28:20.400
Where i ask if you've
thought this through,

28:20.400 --> 28:22.900
And then i rembered,
you don't think things through.

28:23.100 --> 28:24.800
Cold hands,
cold hands.

28:26.100 --> 28:28.000
These people
are dangerous, castle.

28:28.000 --> 28:30.500
You need to stay alert
and focused.

28:30.500 --> 28:32.500
Alert and focused,
got it.

28:32.600 --> 28:34.800
Maybe if--Maybe if you just rubbed 'em
together for a second.

28:34.800 --> 28:36.100
Wait, wait.
Alert and what?

28:37.300 --> 28:38.400
I'm just kidding.

28:38.600 --> 28:40.200
- You're good to go.
- Thanks.

28:40.600 --> 28:43.200
