a black raincoat."

30:28.500 --> 30:31.700
Okay, so they can see you.
That doesn't change anything.

30:40.300 --> 30:41.600
Tell him to
stop fooling around.

30:41.600 --> 30:43.100
Like that'll help.

30:44.600 --> 30:45.600
Okay...

30:46.000 --> 30:49.400
It says,
"cross the street,

30:50.100 --> 30:52.500
And head west
on east 47th."

30:53.100 --> 30:54.400
That's left, right?

30:54.500 --> 30:55.300
Right.

30:55.500 --> 30:57.100
Right, right?
Or right, left?

30:57.100 --> 30:58.600
- Left.
- Left.

31:01.300 --> 31:04.200
"1201 1st."
That's just ahead.

31:05.100 --> 31:06.900
Got it.
We see him.

31:13.800 --> 31:16.800
They want me to leave the bag
at the shoeshine stand

31:16.800 --> 31:19.000
And exit out the side.

31:28.500 --> 31:31.100
All right.
I'm at the stand.

31:31.300 --> 31:32.600
Then have him
make the drop.

31:32.800 --> 31:34.400
Castle,
leave the bag.

31:34.800 --> 31:37.500
Make the drop
and walk away.

31:39.600 --> 31:41.500
Coming in.
Don't have him yet.

31:43.000 --> 31:44.800
I just left it.
I'm headed out.

31:44.800 --> 31:47.100
Esposito, ryan...
you got eyes?

31:47.300 --> 31:49.000
I see the shoeshine stand.

31:49.600 --> 31:51.000
Wait.
I got the backpack.

31:51.100 --> 31:53.500
Asian male... long hair.
I got him, i got him!

31:55.600 --> 31:57.800
Where's the girl?
Where's angela?

31:57.800 --> 31:58.800
What girl?

31:58.900 --> 32:00.900
I don't know
what you're talking about!

32:05.800 --> 32:07.500
Ryan!
Ryan!

32:19.700 --> 32:22.300
The kidnappers
posted an ad on craigslist

32:22.300 --> 32:25.800
And said that this was
a performance art piece for youtube.

32:26.000 --> 32:28.100
They sent out nearly
two dozen of the backpacks.

32:28.100 --> 32:30.600
The poster used
an i.P. Anonymizer,

32:30.600 --> 32:32.600
Making it impossible
to trace.

32:32.700 --> 32:34.600
So we just do nothing?

32:34.800 --> 32:37.000
Well, i managed to¡ìslip the phone

32:37.000 --> 32:39.100
That the kidnappers
gave me inside the backpack.

32:39.100 --> 32:40.500
I don't understand.

32:40.500 --> 32:41.500
Well, before i did that,

32:41.500 --> 32:43.500
I sent a text message
to detective beckett.

32:43.600 --> 32:45.000
The phone's under
a bulk account,

32:45.000 --> 32:46.100
So we can't trace
its owner,

32:46.100 --> 32:47.600
But we can trace its i.D.

32:47.600 --> 32:51.300
So far, we've pinged the phone to
a 20-Block radius on the lower east side.

32:51.300 --> 32:53.800
We'll need another few hours
to narrow it down.

32:53.800 --> 32:56.100
In the meantime, i've moved
a team into the area.

32:56.300 --> 32:57.800
They'll work the streets,
be ready to move

32:57.800 --> 32:59.700
When we have
more information.

33:06.800 --> 33:08.300
- Thanks.
- Mm-Hmm.

33:11.100 --> 33:12.200
You okay?

33:18.500 --> 33:21.200
I keep thinking, if only i saw
who took that bag...

33:21.600 --> 33:23.400
Well, that wasn't
your job.

33:28.100 --> 33:31.400
You know, i can't imagine anything
like this ever happening to alexis.

33:35.100 --> 33:37.100
We'll get her
back soon.

33:37.500 --> 33:39.100
Not as soon as we hoped.

33:39.300 --> 33:41.500
They must've found it,
taken the batteries out.

33:41.600 --> 33:44.100
We just lost the signal
from the phone.

34:07.100 --> 34:08.000
Hey.

34:08.199 --> 34:09.400
Hey...

34:09.600 --> 34:11.900
What are you doing up?
Stressed about finals?

34:12.100 --> 34:14.199
American lit's today.

34:14.500 --> 34:17.500
I was having nightmares
about hester prynne.

34:18.600 --> 34:21.900
The irony for you is not getting
an "a" would cause you shame.

34:22.400 --> 34:23.600
So why are you up?

34:23.699 --> 34:25.900
Looking for a white rabbit.

34:26.000 --> 34:27.800
Lewis carroll
or "the matrix"?

34:27.800 --> 34:29.500
I'm not sure yet.

34:29.600 --> 34:33.400
What did beckett tell you about
taking phone photos at the crime scene?

34:33.600 --> 34:35.699
I don't know.
I wasn't listening.

34:37.100 --> 34:39.400
See all those stuffed
animals on the bed?

34:40.400 --> 34:42.400
It looks just like
mine used to.

34:42.500 --> 34:44.300
Remember when i had
all those animals?

34:44.400 --> 34:46.500
If by rember when,
" you mean monkey-Bonkey,

34:46.500 --> 34:48.900
Who has been washed so many times
he looks like roadkill now,

34:48.900 --> 34:49.500
Then, yes.

34:49.500 --> 34:50.900
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

34:50.900 --> 34:52.400
Oh, then you won't mind
next time i see him

34:52.400 --> 34:54.699
- If i throw him out.
- Don't you dare!

34:55.000 --> 34:56.400
- I won't, i won't.
- Don't.

34:56.500 --> 34:57.500
- I won't.
- Okay.

34:57.500 --> 34:58.600
Okay.

35:01.700 --> 35:04.700
So you think the bunny has
something to do with the case?

35:05.000 --> 35:07.700
I'll let you know when
i go down the rabbit hole.

35:16.700 --> 35:18.000
Castle?

35:18.700 --> 35:19.900
Go back to sleep.

35:20.200 --> 35:21.600
What are you doing?

35:22.000 --> 35:23.500
When alexis was little,

35:23.600 --> 35:26.900
She had a stuffed monkey that
she could not live without.

35:27.000 --> 35:29.200
One time we went on vacation,
she forgot to pack him.

35:29.200 --> 35:30.200
I bought her another one,

35:30.200 --> 35:32.500
But she knew it was
not monkey-Bonkey.

35:32.600 --> 35:33.500
So?

35:33.600 --> 35:38.600
So there's two more pictures of
her clutching this bunny out there.

35:38.700 --> 35:40.300
So where's the bunny?

35:40.500 --> 35:44.100
You think whoever took angela knew
her well enough to take the bunny, too?

35:44.500 --> 35:46.600
But we already checked
the candelas' list.

35:46.600 --> 35:48.400
A couple of teenage babysitters,

35:48.400 --> 35:50.400
A cleaning lady...
they've all been cleared.

35:50.400 --> 35:53.200
Only not all babysitters are teenagers.

35:53.200 --> 35:55.600
Sometimes they're people
close to us.

35:55.700 --> 35:57.400
Sometimes they're family.

35:58.900 --> 36:00.200
When did we lose the signal
on the phone?

36:00.200 --> 36:03.500
Right after we told the candelas
we were tracking it.

36:05.100 --> 36:07.600
Theresa's sister nina--
You got an address?

36:17.600 --> 36:18.900
Nina mendoza,

36:19.100 --> 36:22.100
You're under arrest for
the kidnapping of angela candela.

36:22.200 --> 36:25.000
Taking your own niece?
Put your hands behind your back.

36:25.100 --> 36:27.000
You have the right
to remain silent...

36:27.200 --> 36:28.400
Hello, angela,

36:28.700 --> 36:30.800
I am so happy
to see you.

36:30.900 --> 36:32.500
You wanna go and see mommy?

36:33.100 --> 36:36.900
Come on, baby.
Look at you. Hello.

36:37.500 --> 36:39.200
Hi, beautiful.

36:39.600 --> 36:43.100
You wanna grab your pink rabbit?
Oh, look at the rabbit.

36:58.400 --> 36:59.900
Oh, my god.

37:00.400 --> 37:02.800
Angie!

37:02.900 --> 37:05.700
Mi coraz?N.Mwah!

37:06.100 --> 37:09.700
Oh! Oh! Oh! God.
You look perfect.

37:09.700 --> 37:11.900
Just... perfect!

37:11.900 --> 37:13.800
- Is she okay?
- She's fine. Yeah.

37:14.200 --> 37:17.200
Honey...
what are you doing?

37:17.600 --> 37:19.600
She's here!
She's home!

37:22.400 --> 37:24.300
What is it?
What's wrong?

37:34.400 --> 37:36.000
What's going on?

37:36.700 --> 37:40.600
Crawford...
can you take angela?

37:44.700 --> 37:46.200
Come here,
sweetie.

37:47.700 --> 37:50.600
- Here you go, crawford.
- Thank you. Here we go.

37:55.700 --> 37:57.600
What did you do?

37:58.400 --> 38:01.200
I worked 14-Hour days,
year after year,

38:01.200 --> 38:03.800
Killing myself so that
we can have a life.

38:04.400 --> 38:06.100
And what did you do?

38:07.000 --> 38:08.900
Oh.
You painted.

38:09.500 --> 38:10.900
All you did was paint.

38:10.900 --> 38:13.000
- That's not true.
- Really?

38:13.100 --> 38:14.900
What about that job
you said that you were gonna get

38:14.900 --> 38:16.100
So that i could cut my hours?

38:16.100 --> 38:17.700
I was taking care of angela!

38:17.700 --> 38:20.900
Taking care?
You left her there...

38:21.000 --> 38:23.800
In front of the tv
every day!

38:24.500 --> 38:27.500
Do you know how many times
i woke up to her screams,

38:27.500 --> 38:30.500
Because he was in that room
blasting the music in his ears?

38:30.500 --> 38:32.900
It doesn't give you the right
to kidnap your own child.

38:32.900 --> 38:35.700
How is it kidnapping?
She's my daughter.

38:35.700 --> 38:39.400
Mrs. Candela, you had your sister climb
through that window and take her.

38:40.200 --> 38:41.800
I gave her permission.

38:41.900 --> 38:43.100
It doesn't matter.

38:43.200 --> 38:45.800
You violated your husband's
custodial rights.

38:46.600 --> 38:48.900
Custodial rights?

38:49.000 --> 38:51.800
He didn't even notice
that she was gone!

38:52.100 --> 38:55.700
What kind of a father does that
to his 2-Year-Old child?

38:55.700 --> 38:57.400
Why would you do this?

38:57.400 --> 38:59.800
Why would you put us
through that?

39:00.000 --> 39:02.100
I mean, for god sake,
why not just divorce me?

39:02.100 --> 39:04.900
Oh, so that you can sue me
for alimony?

39:05.400 --> 39:07.900
So that you can get half
of everything?

39:08.100 --> 39:11.400
So that you can get custody
of angela

39:11.600 --> 39:15.900
Because i'm at work all day
and you can "be there for her"?

39:16.000 --> 39:17.200
No.

39:17.400 --> 39:19.600
I've seen what happens
to the guys at work,

39:19.600 --> 39:21.100
What happened to doug ellers.

39:21.200 --> 39:24.100
No way was that
gonna happen to me!

39:24.400 --> 39:26.800
You were paying the ransom
to yourself.

39:30.400 --> 39:35.800
Once angela returned,
i would file for the papers.

39:36.400 --> 39:38.500
There would be nothing left
for him to take.

39:38.500 --> 39:39.700
And if angela was kidnapped

39:39.700 --> 39:41.700
When alfred was
taking care of her, then--

39:41.700 --> 39:42.400
The lawyer said that

39:42.400 --> 39:46.000
If i could prove him negligent,
i would get custody.

39:46.100 --> 39:49.200
I wouldn't have to move out
of the apartment that i paid for

39:49.200 --> 39:52.500
So that he could live here
with my daughter.

39:53.500 --> 39:57.400
Do you know
how hard it was to adopt her,

39:57.600 --> 40:00.000
How much it cost?

40:00.100 --> 40:02.000
Ten years!

40:02.400 --> 40:06.900
How many paintings
have you sold, alfred? Huh?

40:07.400 --> 40:09.200
How many?

40:12.200 --> 40:14.700
How could you
hate me so much?

40:17.000 --> 40:19.200
You made it easy.

40:31.200 --> 40:32.700
So how do you think
she'll do?

40:33.200 --> 40:35.700
Well, it depends on how many
mothers are on the jury.

40:36.700 --> 40:38.200
So...

40:38.900 --> 40:41.000
Now that it's over...

40:42.200 --> 40:44.500
Now that i'm back,
i was...

40:45.000 --> 40:47.600
Thinking maybe we could
give it another shot.

40:48.600 --> 40:50.300
And when you leave again?

40:51.200 --> 40:52.900
You come with me.

41:01.000 --> 41:02.500
Think about it.

41:16.500 --> 41:17.500
Nice guy.

41:19.000 --> 41:21.100
I can see how
it wouldn't work, though.

41:21.700 --> 41:23.700
- Really?
- Sure.

41:24.200 --> 41:27.900
Handsome, square-Jawed,
by-The-Book...

41:27.900 --> 41:29.300
And that's a bad thing?

41:29.400 --> 41:30.800
Yeah, he's like
the male you.

41:31.000 --> 41:33.700
Yin needs yang,
not another yin.

41:33.900 --> 41:36.000
"Yin-Yang" is harmony.

41:36.000 --> 41:39.700
"Yin-Yin" is...
a name for a panda.

41:40.500 --> 41:42.100
Any more wisdom,
obi-Wan?

41:42.100 --> 41:43.900
Nope,
that's it for today.

41:44.000 --> 41:46.000
What say we celebrate
by going out for a drink?

41:46.000 --> 41:47.900
I can't.
I got a date.

41:48.600 --> 41:50.500
A date?
You date?

41:50.900 --> 41:51.800
Who?

41:52.200 --> 41:54.100
That's why it's called
a "private life,"

41:54.100 --> 41:55.600
Because it's private.

41:55.700 --> 41:58.300
Unlike you, i don't live
my life on "page six."

42:00.400 --> 42:02.800
Well, you're a mysterious woman,
detective beckett.

42:02.900 --> 42:06.000
Maybe there's a little more
nikki heat in me than you think.

